Definition: a nuclear reactor that uses water as a coolant and moderator
Example: the water boils in the reactor core and the steam produced can drive a steam turbine
Synonyms: BWR, water-cooled_reactor, a, nuclear, reactor, that, uses, water, as, coolant, and, moderator, the, boils, in, core, steam, produced, can, drive, turbine
Category: noun.artifact
